OL,9,G0445 James Martin's American Adventure
OL,10,     FThe chef begins the Texan leg of
OL,11,     Fhis journey in San Antonio, a city
OL,12,     Fwhich was once part of Mexico.
OL,13,     FHere, James samples traditional
OL,14,     Ftamales and barbecoa at the hands
OL,15,     Fof the city's most famous chef,
OL,16,     FJohnny Hernandez. The chef also
OL,17,     Ftries authentic street food in the
OL,18,     Fform of hot, fresh chorros, and
OL,19,     Flearns about the famous San
OL,20,     FAntonio Chilli Queens
